The paper deals with the problem of schema matching, which is a central challenge in data integration systems. This problem is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, but the focus on data integration and crowdsourcing suggests that cs.DB (Databases) is the most likely category. The use of crowdsourcing also suggests that cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is a relevant sub-category. The paper also deals with the problem of uncertainty reduction, which is relevant to several sub-categories, including cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
